orangelight.title: Generate a report from automated a11y testing
Constituent CDL records have a digital content link, but it doesn't have a viewer.
Generate a report from manual a11y testing

comments.body:
In the case of MMS_ID `99124695833506421` the issue is that both items are within the same holding (`holding_id="22745884920006421"`) and we collapse, by holding id, the information that we return to Orangelight  ([code](https://github.com/pulibrary/bibdata/blob/main/app/adapters/alma_adapter/availability_status.rb#L32-L43)). 

In this case collapsing this data hides from the user the fact that we have two copies and that one of them is on reserves.

We do have the information about both items in the Alma response 

```
{ "pid"=>"23898873500006421", "barcode"=>"32101109060713" ... }
{ "pid"=>"23745884910006421", "barcode"=>"32101104014996" ...} 
```

but both of them come with the exact same location information:

```
"library"=>{"value"=>"lewis", "desc"=>"Lewis Library"}, 
"location"=>{"value"=>"stacks", "desc"=>"Stacks: Lewis Library"},
```

The only indication that one of them is in reserves is in a note field:

```
"internal_note_3"=>"ON_RESERVE: N | RESERVE_CHARGES: 0 | RECALLS_PLACED: 0 | HOLDS_PLACED: 0 | HISTORICAL_BOOKINGS: 0 | SHORT_LOAN_CHARGES: 0 | ", 
```

The original information that we get for this record in the AVA field (in the bibs API endpoint) does indicate that one of the records is in a course reserves locations, but in that response the `holding_id` is not included (see below). 

```
<datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="AVA">
        <subfield code="0">99124695833506421</subfield>
        <subfield code="a">01PRI_INST</subfield>
        <subfield code="b">lewis</subfield>
        <subfield code="c">Course Reserve</subfield>
        <subfield code="d">QB981 . D63 2021</subfield>
        <subfield code="e">available</subfield>
        <subfield code="f">1</subfield>
        <subfield code="g">0</subfield>
        <subfield code="j">res</subfield>
        <subfield code="k">0</subfield>
        <subfield code="p">1</subfield>
        <subfield code="q">Lewis Library</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield ind1=" " ind2=" " tag="AVA">
        <subfield code="0">99124695833506421</subfield>
        <subfield code="8">22745884920006421</subfield>
        <subfield code="a">01PRI_INST</subfield>
        <subfield code="b">lewis</subfield>
        <subfield code="c">Stacks</subfield>
        <subfield code="d">QB981 . D63 2021</subfield>
        <subfield code="e">available</subfield>
        <subfield code="f">1</subfield>
        <subfield code="g">0</subfield>
        <subfield code="j">stacks</subfield>
        <subfield code="k">0</subfield>
        <subfield code="p">2</subfield>
        <subfield code="q">Lewis Library</subfield>
    </datafield>
```

Could we could update OL to display both holdings (the one with a `holding_id` and one without it) ? We could indicate that one of them is in reserves and not include a Request button for it.
